fields.customfield_17644:
Operating at 2.4MHz as specified by Omri 

1. The entire station, mast and parts are still inside the crate - will be shipped as is. When we unpack DS13 it will give us a good idea of required site works. 
2. Mast needs to be decided 
4. install the AC - when onsite by local technician 
5. Calibrate 2 drones 
6. update the servers to the new FW (1.7/1.8) 
7. 2 drones assigned but form part of the returned drones that we need to recover from site and then send to Israel and back again. 5-6 weeks - UAV216 will be repaired in Aust. 
8. Mount and convert isolation switches to metal clad 
9. Convert internal GPO's to Aust. Standards 
10. Convert to single source power supply 
11. Cable up the Aircon 
12. Mount warning labels and test and tag 
13. Order ancillary BOM 
11. There are 12 open services on DS14 that will not be done until DS arrives onsite from shipping. 
12. The following MT's are open and associated with UAV 216 and 220 - SER 3788,3634,3487,3451,3456,3491,3352,3012,2971,2415,3567,2972,3013,2573,3580,2391	15/J
